 can help the university be a good environmental steward  thus minimizing material bound for the landfill and increase our landfill diversion rate to   %  Zero Waste Illinois Law Here you will find what and where you can recycle on campus  more sustainable alternatives  and information about zero waste events Recycling at UIC in Less Than   Minutes This recycling tutorial will walk you through the steps of what and how to recycle at UIC in less than   minutes What materials can be recycled at UIC  Recycling stations of different shapes and sizes can be found in the hallways in every building at UIC and should be no more than a few steps away from your office  classroom or lab  These stations usually consist of three bins   You can recycle paper  broken down cardboard  empty containers of glass and metal  and all plastics with a number except #  PS  polystyrene Buildings with laboratories also have collections for pipette tip boxes  which are #  PP  polypropylene  plastic Certain buildings on campus also have collection bins for batteries  writing utensils  and plastic bags   n      Find out what materials can be recycled at UIC n     How do I recycle at UIC  If you work in an office  you should have a small  blue or grey bin for paper recycling and an even smaller black or grey bin for landfill material  You can empty the blue  desk side recycling bin it into the larger hallway or common area bins whenever it is convenient for you  A Building Service Worker  BSW  will come through to empty the hallway bins If you need assistance obtaining recycling bins for your office contact us at the link at the bottom of the page  n      Steps to properly recycle at UIC n     GSX  Great Stuff Exchange The Great Stuff Exchange  GSX  is an office supplies giveaway program  UIC collects items like binders  desk top filing systems  and other office supplies form departments that can no longer use them and makes them available for students  n      Learn what items you can get for free at GSX n     CERC  Campus Electronic Recycling Collection Each September  there is a centralized collection event for university owned electronics  Simply fill out the appropriate paperwork  bring your items and a copy of the FABWEB disposal request  n      Discover how to properly recycle electronic products at UIC n     LabShare Program  and plastic pipettes and centrifuge tubes  The LabShare program also accepts equipment without university property tags   Researchers may request these items for use in the lab  n      Find out how to donate or obtain used lab supplies n     Zero Waste Events  This means reusable  compostable  or recyclable materials are used when needed  You are also participating in resource recovery for donating untouched  packaged items  Carefully differentiating between each material and recognizing the exact materials used may seem like a lot of work  however  we are here to help you through your zero waste event planning The UIC Zero Waste Planning Guide includes a case study for an example  definitions  a list of operations to be done before  during  and after your event  and a list of sustainable resources  With careful  thought out planning  zero waste is easy and sustainable   n      Check out this page for resources how to create a zero waste event at UIC  n     Sustainable Purchasing It all starts with smart materials  If an item  for example  Styrofoam cups  is provided for use on campus Choosing materials with more recycled content helps the economy and the environment  n      Follow these steps to purchase the most sustainable materials for use on campus n     Questions about the Recycling Program  Contact Us  recycling uic edu Additional Recycling Related Resources  n n n            Join the CCSE Sustainable Materials Subcommittee n         n n                The Chancellor s Committee on Sustainability   Energy s Grounds subcommittee discusses n             n n  n n n            Zero Waste Campus n         n n                Th